description:
Update cmd/ticker/main.go for new TUI:

The new TUI should be a drop-in replacement. Verify:

1. tui.New(cfg) creates Model correctly
2. Message types match what engine sends:
   - tui.OutputMsg(string)
   - tui.IterationStartMsg{Iteration, TaskID, TaskTitle}
   - tui.IterationEndMsg{Iteration, Cost, Tokens}
   - tui.SignalMsg{Signal, Reason}
   - tui.ErrorMsg{Err}
   - tui.RunCompleteMsg{Reason, Signal, Iterations, Cost}
   - tui.TasksUpdateMsg{Tasks}

3. tui.TaskInfo and tui.TaskStatus match what ticksClient returns

4. tui.EpicInfo and tui.Picker for epic selection

5. p.Send() calls work with new message types

6. pauseChan communication works bidirectionally

Test with: go build ./cmd/ticker && ./ticker run --auto
